Body mainly dark brown to black with several pale maculae (
Fig. 3
); vertex hexagonal (
Fig. 3B, E
); frons with strong median carina and central plate with pale heart-shaped macula (
Fig. 3A, D
); clypeus extending anteriorly, produced into slight snout (
Fig. 3C, F
); lateral lobe of pronotum with three to four sensory pits arranged in a row (
Fig. 3C, F
); abdominal tergites (
Fig. 3C, F
, 
26B
) with row of sensory pits followed by single isolated ventral sensory pit (tergite IV) or by isolated pair of diagonally aligned ventral sensory pits (tergites V to VII).

